---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getMeta, prettyDate } from '../lib/data.mjs';
const meta = getMeta();
const title = `Privacy Policy | ${meta.title}`;
const description = `How ${meta.title} handles data: a static reference site with no accounts and no personal-data collection by us, plus how advertising cookies work if ads are enabled, and your choices.`;
const updated = prettyDate(meta.generated_at);
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} noindex={false}>
  <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" style="font-size:.9rem;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-bottom:6px">
    <a href="/">Home</a> &rsaquo; <span>Privacy</span>
  </nav>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="lead">{meta.title} is a static reference website. We keep this simple because we collect
    very little: there are no accounts, and the calculators run entirely in your browser.</p>
  <p class="source-note">Last updated {updated}.</p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>{meta.title} publishes reference data on statutory, judgment, and tax interest rates. The site is a
    set of static pages served over HTTPS. You can reach us at
    <a href="mailto:privacy@statuterates.com">privacy@statuterates.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <ul class="clean">
    <li><strong>Nothing you type stays with us.</strong> The interest calculators compute in your
      browser (client-side JavaScript). The amounts and dates you enter are never sent to us or stored.</li>
    <li><strong>No accounts, no sign-up, no marketing emails.</strong> We don't ask for your name,
      email, or any personal information to use the site.</li>
    <li><strong>Standard server logs.</strong> Like almost all websites, our hosting and content-delivery
      providers (currently Cloudflare and GitHub Pages) automatically record basic technical requests —
      IP address, browser type, and the page requested — to deliver the site and protect it from abuse.
      We do not use these logs to identify you.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Advertising &amp; cookies</h2>
  <p>This site is supported by display advertising. When advertising is enabled, we use
    <strong>Google AdSense</strong>, a third-party advertising service provided by Google LLC. To show
    ads, Google and its partners may:</p>
  <ul class="clean">
    <li>Use cookies and similar technologies (including the DoubleClick/Google advertising cookie) to
      serve ads based on your prior visits to this and other websites.</li>
    <li>Collect information such as your IP address, device and browser information, and interactions
      with ads, in accordance with <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google's advertising policies</a>.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits. You can
    opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
    <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>,
    and opt out of some third-party vendors' use of cookies at
    <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info/choices</a>
    (or <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">youronlinechoices.eu</a>
    in Europe). You can also block or delete cookies in your browser settings; the site's data and
    calculators will still work.</p>

  <h2>If you are in the EEA, UK, or Switzerland</h2>
  <p>Where required, we present a consent choice (via Google's certified consent management) before any
    advertising cookies that require consent are set, and ads are shown on a non-personalized basis if
    you do not consent. You have the right to access, correct, or erase personal data, and to withdraw
    consent, under the GDPR/UK GDPR. Google acts as an independent controller for the advertising data
    it processes; see <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>If you are in California</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal information for money. Some sharing of advertising identifiers with ad
    partners may qualify as a "sale" or "sharing" under the CCPA/CPRA; you can opt out using the tools
    above (Google Ads Settings and aboutads.info). California residents may request access to or deletion
    of personal information by emailing <a href="mailto:privacy@statuterates.com">privacy@statuterates.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>We use <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> for privacy-respecting, aggregate traffic measurement.
    It is cookieless, sets no client-side identifier, does not fingerprint you or track you across sites, and
    collects no personal data — it simply counts page views so we can see which pages are useful. We do not
    build advertising profiles from it.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>This is a general-audience reference site and is not directed to children under 13. We do not
    knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>Because we don't collect personal data through the site, there is nothing for us to retain about
    you. Server logs held by our infrastructure providers are kept only as long as those providers'
    standard security and operational policies require.</p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy as the site evolves (for example, when advertising is turned on or a new
    provider is added). The "last updated" date above reflects the current version.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about this policy or your data? Email
    <a href="mailto:privacy@statuterates.com">privacy@statuterates.com</a>.</p>

  <div class="disclaimer">Reference data only — not legal, tax, or financial advice. See our
    <a href="/terms/">Terms &amp; Disclaimer</a>.</div>
</BaseLayout>
